o.com/new-index-status-enhance-your-seo-visibility-by-ensuring-all-your-urls-are-indexed/\">[New] Index Status: Enhance Your SEO Visibility By Ensuring All Your URLs Are Indexed</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Benjamin Rojas\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8843:\"<p>Were back with another exciting announcement!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Introducing Index Status in AIOSEO 4.5.0.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This powerful feature lets you easily see whether Google has indexed your URLs.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-gray-light-background-color has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-indexing-and-why-is-it-important\">What is Indexing, and Why is it Important?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-is-index-status\">What is Index Status?</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-supercharge-your-rankings-with-index-status\">Supercharge Your Rankings with Index Status</a></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"Introducing Search Engine Indexing Status in WordPress\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/lq_QPMySnu4?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-what-is-indexing-and-why-is-it-important\">What is Indexing, and Why is it Important?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When you publish a post or page on your website, search engines have to discover it. To do this, they <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-crawling-and-indexing/\" title=\"What is Crawling and Indexing in SEO? [Beginners Guide]\">crawl your website</a> to find your URLs. Once theyve crawled a URL, they put it in an index.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Indexing in search engine optimization (SEO) refers to the process search engines use to collect, analyze, and store information from web pages. This information is stored in a database called an index.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Indexing means that the search engine has added the page to its database and can now retrieve and display it in relevant search results when users query your keyword.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is important because it increases your visibility in search results, resulting in more traffic to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Because knowing the index status of your URLs is important, many of you have been asking for a way to easily see that from your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thats why were so excited to announce Index Status.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-what-is-index-status\">What is Index Status?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Index Status is a new feature in AIOSEO that shows you the indexing status of your web pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-theme-notice-box\" role=\"alert\">\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Index Status is only available on the Elite plan.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see the index status of your web pages in the AIOSEO Details section on the <strong>Posts</strong> page of your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"410\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-2-1024x410.png\" alt=\"Index Status in the AIOSEO Details section.\" class=\"wp-image-245422\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-2-1024x410.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-2-300x120.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-2-768x307.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-2-1536x615.png 1536w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-2-2048x820.png 2048w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-2-600x240.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also see it in the Content Performance sections of Search Statistics and the Content Rankings report.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"440\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-1.png\" alt=\"Index Status in the Content Performance report.\" class=\"wp-image-245421\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-1.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-1-300x188.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-1-600x376.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And when you hover your cursor over the index status, you get more information about that URL.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"348\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-extra-info.png\" alt=\"Additional URL information shown by the Index Status feature.\" class=\"wp-image-245423\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-extra-info.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-extra-info-300x149.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-extra-info-600x297.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This includes:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Last Crawl</strong>: The date the URL was crawled</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Crawled As</strong>: The user agent that crawled the page (mobile or desktop user agent)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Crawl Allowed</strong>: Whether crawling for that URL is permitted in your robots.txt file</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Indexing allowed</strong>: Whether indexing for that URL is permitted by the robots.txt meta</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Page Fetch</strong>: Whether fetching of the page was successful</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>It also shows the user-declared and Google-selected canonicals.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All this vital information helps you understand how Google indexes your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"aioseo-supercharge-your-rankings-with-index-status\">Supercharge Your Rankings with Index Status</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Index Status is a powerful feature that can help boost your search rankings. One way it does that is by letting you easily notice URLs that are not indexed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This allows you to quickly troubleshoot any indexing issues that a URL may have. As a result, you increase your chances of ranking as all your content will be indexed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides this significant update, weve made several notable improvements to many features you love. For example, the <strong>AIOSEO Details</strong> section on the <strong>Posts</strong> overview page in WordPress has been revamped.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Apart from the Index Status and TruSEO score, it now also shows the Headline Analyzer score. Plus, you can now change your <strong>Title</strong> and <strong>Description</strong> using smart tags right in the <strong>AIOSEO Details</strong> section.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"577\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-aioseo-details-new.png\" alt=\"Changes to the AIOSEO Details section.\" class=\"wp-image-245424\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-aioseo-details-new.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-aioseo-details-new-300x247.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/post-index-status-aioseo-details-new-600x493.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see all our changes in our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/changelog/\">full product changelog</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What are you waiting for?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Update your site to AIOSEO 4.5.0 to unlock these powerful new features and rank your content higher on SERPs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if youre not yet using AIOSEO, make sure to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">install and activate the plugin today</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have questions about these features, please comment below or <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/contact/\" title=\"Contact Us\">contact our customer support team</a>. Were always ready to help. Our commitment to making AIOSEO the easiest and best WordPress SEO plugin is only getting stronger as we continue to win as a team with you, our customers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Were so grateful for your continued support, feedback, and suggestions. Please keep those suggestions and feature requests coming!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope you enjoy using these new SEO features as much as we enjoyed creating them.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>-Benjamin Rojas (President of AIOSEO).</em></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/new-index-status-enhance-your-seo-visibility-by-ensuring-all-your-urls-are-indexed/\">[New] Index Status: Enhance Your SEO Visibility By Ensuring All Your URLs Are Indexed</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1